WEBVTT

00:01.000 --> 00:05.000
Click to 'Additional tools' header menu item
and select 'Debian FAI' in expanded list

00:05.000 --> 00:07.000
Click on blue header 'Debian settings' 
to see main configuration

00:07.000 --> 00:20.000
Change values to correct 
according your needs

00:20.000 --> 00:22.000
Click on 'Debian settings' again
to collapse

00:22.000 --> 00:24.000
Click on blue header 'HDD split' 
to see partition disk config

00:24.000 --> 00:32.000
You could add, edit sizes or order 
of the following disk parts

00:32.000 --> 00:35.000
Let's add new part for /opt part
Click to plus button for this

00:35.000 --> 00:37.000
Select partition name
(it's Opt in our case)

00:37.000 --> 00:40.000
And select the most convenient 
file system for new partition

00:40.000 --> 00:43.000
Type good size for this part
(size, which would be enough)

00:43.000 --> 00:45.000
And click OK button
(the nearest btn at the bottom)

00:45.000 --> 00:47.000
New part appeared in the list.
You could move it to new place

00:47.000 --> 00:50.000
Or change order of existing

00:50.000 --> 00:56.000
Of course, you could remove
some parts if you wish

00:56.000 --> 00:59.000
Mouse double click if for edit partition

00:59.000 --> 01:11.000
Edit them

01:11.000 --> 01:13.500
You should click 'Accept' button
to agree with changes

01:13.500 --> 01:15.500
or 'Restore to default' to get back
to default state 

01:16.000 --> 01:43.000
I'm adding all unlisted partition types
and 'Accept' that

01:44.000 --> 01:49.500
You are able to see result of changes
(that's preseed.cfg file if you know I mean)

01:50.000 --> 01:58.000
Click 'Get Image' button to download debian image
(please be patient and wait, that's pretty time consuming)